<div class="comment" id="comment-47765473">
  <div class="comment_head"><a href="/user/rkozik1989">rkozik1989</a> 1 day ago</div>
  <div class="comment_text">Good on you for quitting, but unless you know of people in your network who&#x27;re willing to buy what you&#x27;re making not sure if this will work. Often times its the simplest ideas that make the most profitable businesses. You know, like selling handmade soap or coffee. The problem with what you&#x27;re doing is you are trying to enter a market as the first person doing it. Which means nobody has taken the risk to prove there is a demand, and without that it means you&#x27;re potentially burning a ton of time and resources with no logical place to pivot to next.</div>
  
